## Technical Details

### Why `flex-1 min-h-0` Works

The Calendar widget container uses `h-full flex flex-col` (Calendar.tsx:334):
```tsx
<div className="calendar-widget h-full flex flex-col">
  {/* Navigation */}
  {/* Views */}
</div>
```

Without the wrapper, views had `flex: 1 1 auto` (default) but `min-height: auto`, which allowed them to grow beyond the container's height, forcing page scrolling.

With `flex-1 min-h-0`:
- `flex-1` = `flex: 1 1 0%` (grow to fill space, shrink if needed, basis 0%)
- `min-h-0` = `min-height: 0` (allow shrinking below content size)
- Result: Views constrained to available height, enabling internal scrolling

